To solve this, we first find the norm of $\mathbf{v}$.
\begin{align*} \|\mathbf{v}\| &= 4 \\ \|\mathbf{v}\|^2 &= \|\mathbf{v}\|\cdot\mathbf{v} \\ 16 &= \mathbf{v}^2 \end{align*}
Now we use this relationship to find the norm of $-3\mathbf{v}$.
\begin{align*} \|{-3 \mathbf{v}}\| &= {-3 \mathbf{v}}\cdot{-3 \mathbf{v}} \\ & = 9\mathbf{v}^2 \\ &= 9\cdot16 \\ & = \boxed{144} \end{align*}
answer: $144$
By the way, the answer to the absolute value of $-3x - 4$ for $x < 2$ is $3x + 4$. This is because the answer to finding those values of $x$ where $x<2$ is all values less than $2$; the answer is $!3x-4^!$ equals the answer $!20!$

